column12: The 1400 MHz fluxes are from Camilo et al. 2000
The 400 and 2000 MHz fluxes are from the refs in PSRCAT.
There doesn't seem to be any more fluxes in the literature for this cluster.
We have 14/29 pulsar fluxes in this cluster :(
One thing to bear in mind with this cluster is that the pulsars scintillate a ton!
So we really need to average MANY observations to get more reliable fluxes.
The ones we have here may not actually be that useful.
NGC 362 pulsars all listed as unpublished as of 08/29/2023
S400 and S2000 from Friere et al. 2007. S1400 scaled from other fluxes
Flux densities to right from Ridolfi et al. 2022, in the MeerKAT UHF band (544-1087 MHz)
S1400 values from Dai et al. 2020
No value for other psrs in this cluster found in other papers
S1500 and SI from Lynch & Ransom, 2011

S1400 - Possenti et al. 2003; S2000 - Lynch et al. 2012
